commentary: Aleph hard to read because of the supralinear waw. Perhaps the scribe first tried to delete the aleph before adding the waw.
On the IAA image (483832) there has been some material lost, and we cannot make a complete reading here. However, by consulting the PAM 42383 or PAM 43269, we can make a reading of גבהו[ות]
This is the height and width and thus it should go into a different SQL table about the artefact and not the characters
